Spontaneous contrast in the pericardial sac caused by gas-forming organisms.
 Purulent pericarditis is a life-threatening disease associated with a variety of microorganisms.
 The case presented herein has unusual manifestations of contrast echoes on two-dimensional echocardiography.
 To our knowledge, this is the first reported case of pericarditis caused by gas-forming group D Streptococcus and Klebsiella pneumoniae with pyopericardium, resulting in contrast echoes on the two-dimensional echocardiographic image.
